1528/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-womens-cycling-bibs-and-shorts-696x474.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131528/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-womens-cycling-bibs-and-shorts-1068x728.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131528/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-womens-cycling-bibs-and-shorts-617x420.jpg 617w\"></a></p><p>For the women’s version, all of the technology is the same, but the design differs slightly. The legs are a bit shorter, and the gripper section is 1cm shorter (6cm versus 7cm). The bibstraps are a bit wider, and there’s also a strapless shorts version, too. They also get a women’s specific pad.</p><h3>Ride Review:</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3.jpg\" alt=\"2021 castelli premio black cycling bibshorts for men and women\" width=\"1550\" height=\"1047\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3.jpg 1550w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-297x201.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-800x540.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-120x81.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-768x519.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-1536x1038.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-696x470.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-1068x721.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-622x420.jpg 622w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1550px) 100vw, 1550px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3.jpg 1550w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-297x201.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-800x540.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-120x81.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-768x519.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-1536x1038.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-696x470.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-1068x721.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131522/castelli-premio-black-ultralight-bibshorts-3-622x420.jpg 622w\"></a></p><p>Basically, they live up to the hype Castelli is surrounding them with. We’ve been out on a number of long, hard, and fast rides in them and they are indeed quite comfortable.</p><p>They’re also light, and quite supportive. The banded legs and seamless gripper edge stay in place, never once creeping up unintentionally. Even better, I never had to adjust them for comfort…the gripper keeps them in place without pulling on my skin.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-large-leaderboard-2\"></span></p><p>The straps are appropriately wide and comfortable, too. And they’re long enough. I’m testing an XL, which worked great for my 6’2″ frame of average proportions. It’s worth noting that some Castelli “XL” items in the past have been laughably tight and small, clearly marked in European (and Italian specifically) “XL” sizing, not American.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-leader-1\"></span></p><figure id=\"attachment_259782\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-259782\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021.jpg\" alt=\"castelli climbers jersey has longer sleeves for more aerodynamic sun protection\" width=\"1154\" height=\"651\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021.jpg 1154w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-297x168.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-800x451.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-768x433.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-696x393.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-1068x602.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-745x420.jpg 745w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1154px) 100vw, 1154px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021.jpg 1154w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-297x168.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-800x451.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-768x433.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-696x393.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-1068x602.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/24131447/castelli-climbers-jersey-ultralight-road-cycling-jersey-2021-745x420.jpg 745w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-259782\">The Castelli Climber’s Jersey has longer sleeves, which are great for aerodynamics and sun protection, yet it’s still super lightweight.</figcaption></figure><p>Paired with the ultralight <a href=\"https://www.castelli-cycling.com/us/men/tops/cycling-jerseys/p/452101221P-364\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Climber’s Jersey</a>, which has a claimed weight of just 107g, they make for a perfect kit on hot summer days. The jersey is nearly see-through, so it’s very breathable, yet I didn’t get sunburned through it. The longer sleeves come all the way down, covering my entire upper arm right to the top of the elbow, too. I love it, but shorter riders might find them a little long.</p><p>If you’re looking for a fresh set of bibshorts for summer and want something that’s supportive, cool, and comfortable over the long haul, the new Castelli Premio Black are worth a look.</p><p>Retail is $259.99, and they’ll be available in black at launch, with a very dark Savile Blue color following a few weeks later. Available now at ColoradoCyclist.com and CompetitiveCyclist.com.</p><p><a href=\"http://castelli-cycling.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Castelli-Cycling.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"81b3b3a9a7b471a7938d5c469f54400f22dc562f723e443f1332044fffaa4f08","category":"Cycling"}